ention the late phases. This publication tackles this issue by analysing and reassessing the available evidence for the late phases of the Hispanic aqueducts by looking at a wide range of sources of information, many times derived from the recent interest shown by archaeologists and researchers on late antique urbanism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAqueductszPortugalxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aAqueductszSpainxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aUrbanizationzPortugalxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aUrbanizationzSpainxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAntiquities & Archaeology. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Antiquities & Archaeology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066151440uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324070740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463240707423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463240707/original  a978-3-11-066151-4  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK